File: Nursing practitioners do a swab that will be submitted to labs for analysis. PRETORIA - Dis-Chem has introduced drive-through testing services for COVID-19 at nine of its pharmacies across the country. Nursing practitioners do a swab that will be submitted to labs for analysis. The list is available on the company's website. READ: Drive-through or queue: The dilemma of virus testing in SA The process is simple: Customers drive in, register and drive through to a pay point where the customer pays R850 before the test is performed. Dis-Chem said it exercises all necessary precautions while performing the tests. Lizeth Kruger, a Dis-Chem National Clinic manager said, “that’s exactly why we have this drive testing so that you don’t have to get out of your car so you minimise the contact." LIST: Lancet Labs which offer COVID-19 tests 48 hours later, clients get their results with a simple phone call. Doctors are available for counselling telephonically. Kruger has encouraged people to continue adhering to the lockdown, to keep clean and stay safe. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.